Vice President Mike Pence delivered a speech in Artesia, New Mexico, where he praised the American energy industry and called for the passage of the United States-Mexico-Canada Agreement (USMCA). He highlighted the Trump administration's efforts to promote American energy independence, including rolling back regulations and cutting taxes. Pence emphasized the importance of the USMCA in supporting American energy companies and creating jobs. He urged the audience to contact their representatives in Congress to push for the passage of the trade deal. Pence also expressed opposition to the Green New Deal and called for continued support for American energy independence.